density as space-time.

43
00:01:38,797 --> 00:01:41,598
So what do you think? What do
you think? So what do you think?

44
00:01:44,769 --> 00:01:46,770
Hmm...

45
00:01:46,772 --> 00:01:48,372
What? Is it wrong?

46
00:01:48,374 --> 00:01:49,873
Have you seen it somewhere else?

47
00:01:52,176 --> 00:01:54,378
Hmm...

48
00:01:55,213 --> 00:01:56,480
I know this isn't my area,

49
00:01:56,482 --> 00:01:58,648
and I could never
do the math like you can,

50
00:01:58,650 --> 00:02:00,384
but could this be something...?

51
00:02:00,386 --> 00:02:01,386
Well...

52
00:02:03,689 --> 00:02:07,290
You could have set Newton's
gravitational constant to one.

53
00:02:07,292 --> 00:02:09,659
And, ugh, the whole thing reeks
of blueberry.

54
00:02:09,661 --> 00:02:12,562
You know I can't stand
these scented markers.

55
00:02:13,364 --> 00:02:15,866
No one told you to taste them.

56
00:02:16,734 --> 00:02:18,835
Come on, is-is this
good or not?

57
00:02:20,472 --> 00:02:21,938
It's good.

58
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:23,707
Really?
I like it.

59
00:02:23,709 --> 00:02:25,108
I think you're on to something.

60
00:02:25,110 --> 00:02:26,410
